Package         Astarte_Hierarchy 

                Export
=================================================================

=================================================================
%% This package describes the standard genus/community hieararchy.
=================================================================

<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<

The following diagram shows the standard genera and commmunities
(all upper case) and their relationships to one another, 
and to standard species and families.  Larger genera are to 
the left.  Meets should be obvious.

The special thing PAIR refers to cartesian products (ordered 
pairs).  Since PAIR is in genus ORDER, species (S,T) is in
genus ORDER for all species S and T where S and T are also
in genus ORDER. Ordering on pairs and lists is lexicographic.
For example, [2,3,6] < [2,4,5] and (2,3,6) < (2,4,5).

Genera and communities marked with a * are not extensible.  
Genus ANY includes all species -- it is implicitly extended any 
time a new species or genus is added.  Genera RANKED and ENUMERATED 
are extended any time an enumerated species is created.  
You cannot extend them directly.

Communities OPAQUE and TRANSPARENT cannot be extended directly.
They are extended any time a new family or community is created.
Communities and families that are part of OPAQUE are opaque.  Those
that are part of TRANSPARENT are transparent.

